sentences: Teru joined Aikaryu (藍華柳) in 2002, replacing guitarist Death.
In August 2003 they signed to Crow Music (the same label as Hizaki's band Crack Brain) and released their first single the following month.
But in early 2006, they were involved in a car accident with most members having serious injuries.
But in April 2007, they decided to disband.
Teru joined Hizaki's solo band, Hizaki Grace Project, in October 2006.
They released three albums; Dignity of Crest, Ruined Kingdom and Curse of Virgo, and on December 24, 2007 had their latest live performance.
In 2007, he was recruited for Versailles by Hizaki and Kamijo, after being recommended by the Rock May-Kan venue.
He even gave a lecture at a seminar on the development of Japanese pop culture, held by the Kyoto University of Art and Design on November 25, 2010.
He also designed the artwork for the 2015 album, Venom, by American heavy metal band, Impellitteri.
In January 2011, he and the rest of Versailles started starring in their own TV mini drama called Onegai Kanaete Versailles (おねがいかなえてヴェルサイユ, "Fulfill My Wish Versailles").
Both Teru and Hizaki participated in the Blue Planet Japan project, which was created in response to the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami.
On August 9, 2011, the second anniversary of Jasmine You's death, Teru composed and dedicated the song "「For You」" to his former bandmate.
On July 20, 2012, Versailles announced they were stopping all activities at the end of the year.
On April 1, 2013, every member of Versailles minus singer Kamijo announced they had formed a new band named Jupiter.

Before Versailles he was previously in Aikaryu and supported his future bandmate Hizaki in his solo project.
In August 2003 they signed to Crow Music (the same label as Hizaki's band Crack Brain) and released their first single the following month.
For the next three years they toured extensively, had numerous releases and several line-up changes.
In December Aikaryu regrouped and performed a small tour.
In 2007, he was recruited for Versailles by Hizaki and Kamijo, after being recommended by the Rock May-Kan venue.

Teru is also an artist, having designed many releases for Kamijo's record label Sherow Artist Society under the alias "Wait a Minute" (stylized as wait A minute), including for Versailles, Hizaki Grace Project and Matenrou Opera.
The show also starred Rina Koike and aired on Mainichi Broadcasting System and TV Kanagawa until March.
They performed live at Shibuya O-West on June 25 and released the single "Hitotsu Dake ~We are the One~" on September 14, with the proceeds from the single donated to the victims.
On July 20, 2012, Versailles announced they were stopping all activities at the end of the year.
They recruited Zin as vocalist and released their debut single, "Blessing of the Future", in the summer.
